 The  .env  file is used to store the environment variables. The  serviceAccountKey.json  file is used to store the Firebase service account key. 
 Step 3: Install the required packages 
 To install the required packages, run the following command: 
 npm install express cors firebase-admin dotenv 
 Step 4: Create the Firebase project 
 To create a Firebase project, follow the steps below: 
 
 Go to the  Firebase Console. 
 Click on the  Add project  button. 
 Enter the project name and click on the  Continue  button. 
 Click on the  Create project  button. 
 
 Step 5: Create a Firebase service account 
 To create a Firebase service account, follow the steps below: 
 
 Go to the  Firebase Console. 
 Click on the project name. 
 Click on the  Project settings  icon. 
 Click on the  Service accounts  tab. 
 Click on the  Generate new private key  button. 
 Click on the  Generate key  button. 
 Save the  serviceAccountKey.json  file. 
 
 Step 6: Create the  .env  file 
 Create a new file named  .env  in the project root directory and add the following content: 
 FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-firebase-project-id